<%= image_tag('fabricipsum.png', style:"height: 125px; width: 125px") %>

<h1>Fabric Ipsum</h1>

<section class="intro-wrapper">
  <div class="left-half">
    <p>If you are looking for fabric auto-generated text to fill up your web pages, you've come to the perfect place. Who wants a boring ipsum? Not me! So, let's add some character to all the things with fabric!<p>
  </div>

  <div class="right-half">
    <p>Fabric Ipsum is a fabric word generator, covering all words that are fabric related.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<%= form_with url: generate_path, local: true do |f| %>
  <p>
    I want <%= f.select 'num', (1..5) %> paragraphs of fabric placeholder text.
  </p>

  <p>
    <%= f.submit 'Fabricfy!', data: { disable_with: false } %>
  </p>

  <% @paragraph_arr.each do |paragraph| %>
    <p><%= paragraph %></p>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
